{"id":"datalinq-general-ifelse","name":null,"description":null,"code":"<div class=\"navbar\">\r\n  <div class=\"title\" id=\"function-title\"><a href=\"https://localhost:7277/datalinq/report/datalinq-guide@select-all-users@index\">DataLinq: If/Else clauses</a></div>\r\n  <div style=\"width: 30px;\"></div> \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"wrapper\">\r\n\r\n    @{\r\n        var condition = true;\r\n        var conditionInt = 1;\r\n        var conditionString = \"DataLinq\";\r\n    }\r\n\r\n<button class=\"collapsible\">\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-label\">If clause</span>\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-actions\">\r\n<span class=\"action-button\" onclick=\"openPopup(event, 'if_if')\">Code/Query</span>\r\n</span>\r\n</button>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n    <h1>bool</h1>\r\n    @if(condition)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>DataLinq</p>\r\n    }\r\n    @if(!condition)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>Negated DataLinq</p>\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    <h1>int</h1>\r\n    @if(conditionInt == 1)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>DataLinq</p>\r\n    }\r\n    @if(conditionInt != 1)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>Negated DataLinq</p>\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    <h1>string</h1>\r\n    @if(conditionString.Equals(\"DataLinq\"))\r\n    {\r\n        <p>DataLinq</p>\r\n    }\r\n    @if(!conditionString.Equals(\"DataLinq\"))\r\n    {\r\n        <p>Negated DataLinq</p>\r\n    }\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"description_if_if\" hidden>\r\nde: Die if-Anweisung wird verwendet, um bedingte Logik in einer Razor-Ansicht zu implementieren. \r\nSie prüft, ob eine Bedingung wahr oder falsch ist, und führt den entsprechenden Codeblock aus. \r\nIn diesem Beispiel werden verschiedene Bedingungen auf unterschiedliche Datentypen (bool, int, string) angewendet\r\n\r\nbool     Wenn condition wahr ist, wird \"DataLinq\" angezeigt. Andernfalls, wenn condition falsch ist, wird \"Negated DataLinq\" angezeigt.\r\n\r\nint      Wenn conditionInt den Wert 1 hat, wird \"DataLinq\" angezeigt. Wenn der Wert jedoch nicht 1 ist, wird \"Negated DataLinq\" angezeigt.\r\n\r\nstring   Wenn conditionString den Wert \"DataLinq\" hat, wird \"DataLinq\" angezeigt. Andernfalls wird \"Negated DataLinq\" angezeigt.\r\n\r\nen: The if statement is used to implement conditional logic in a Razor view. \r\nIt checks whether a condition is true or false and executes the corresponding code block.\r\nIn this example, different conditions are applied to different data types (bool, int, string)\r\n\r\nbool     If condition is true, \"DataLinq\" will be displayed. Otherwise, if condition is false, \"Negated DataLinq\" will be displayed.\r\n\r\nint      If conditionInt equals 1, \"DataLinq\" will be displayed. If the value is not 1, \"Negated DataLinq\" will be displayed.\r\n\r\nstring   If conditionString equals \"DataLinq\", \"DataLinq\" will be displayed. Otherwise, \"Negated DataLinq\" will be displayed.\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"csharp_if_if\" hidden><script type=\"text/plain\">\r\n@@{\r\n     var condition = true;\r\n     var conditionInt = 1;\r\n     var conditionString = \"DataLinq\";\r\n}\r\n\r\n<h1>bool</h1>\r\n@@if(condition)\r\n{\r\n    <p>DataLinq</p>\r\n}\r\n@@if(!condition)\r\n{\r\n    <p>Negated DataLinq</p>\r\n}\r\n<h1>int</h1>\r\n@@if(conditionInt == 1)\r\n{\r\n    <p>DataLinq</p>\r\n}\r\n@@if(conditionInt != 1)\r\n{\r\n    <p>Negated DataLinq</p>\r\n}\r\n<h1>string</h1>\r\n@@if(conditionString.Equals(\"DataLinq\"))\r\n{\r\n    <p>DataLinq</p>\r\n}\r\n@@if(!conditionString.Equals(\"DataLinq\"))\r\n{\r\n    <p>Negated DataLinq</p>\r\n}\r\n</script></div>\r\n<div id=\"sql_if_if\" hidden></div>\r\n\r\n<button class=\"collapsible\">\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-label\">If/Else clause</span>\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-actions\">\r\n<span class=\"action-button\" onclick=\"openPopup(event, 'if_ifElse')\">Code/Query</span>\r\n</span>\r\n</button>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n    @if(conditionInt == 0)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>Equals 0</p>\r\n    } else {\r\n        <p>Equals 1</p>\r\n    }\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"description_if_ifElse\" hidden>\r\nde: Die if-else-Anweisung prüft, ob eine Bedingung wahr oder falsch ist, und führt den entsprechenden Codeblock aus.\r\nIn diesem Beispiel wird überprüft, ob der Wert von conditionInt gleich 0 ist. Falls ja, wird \"Equals 0\" angezeigt, andernfalls wird \"Equals 1\" angezeigt.\r\nen: The if-else statement checks whether a condition is true or false and executes the corresponding code block.\r\nIn this example, it checks whether the value of conditionInt is equal to 0. If true, it displays \"Equals 0\"; otherwise, it displays \"Equals 1\".\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"csharp_if_ifElse\" hidden><script type=\"text/plain\">\r\n@@{\r\n     var condition = true;\r\n     var conditionInt = 1;\r\n     var conditionString = \"DataLinq\";\r\n}\r\n\r\n@@if(conditionInt == 0)\r\n{\r\n    <p>Equals 0</p>\r\n} else {\r\n    <p>Equals 1</p>\r\n}\r\n</script></div>\r\n<div id=\"sql_if_ifElse\" hidden></div>\r\n\r\n<button class=\"collapsible\">\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-label\">If/IfElse/Else clause</span>\r\n<span class=\"collapsible-actions\">\r\n<span class=\"action-button\" onclick=\"openPopup(event, 'if_ifElseIfElse')\">Code/Query</span>\r\n</span>\r\n</button>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n    @if(conditionInt == 0)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>Equals 0</p>\r\n    } else if(conditionInt == 1)\r\n    {\r\n        <p>Equals 1</p>\r\n    } else {\r\n        <p>Equals something else</p>\r\n    }\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"description_if_ifElseIfElse\" hidden>\r\nde: Mit if, else if und else können mehrere Bedingungen überprüft werden. Hier wird geprüft, ob conditionInt gleich 0 ist, dann 1 – und wenn beides nicht zutrifft, wird \"Equals something else\" angezeigt.\r\nen: Using if, else if, and else allows checking multiple conditions. In this example, it checks if conditionInt is 0, then 1 – and if neither is true, it displays \"Equals something else\".\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"csharp_if_ifElseIfElse\" hidden><script type=\"text/plain\">\r\n@@{\r\n     var condition = true;\r\n     var conditionInt = 1;\r\n     var conditionString = \"DataLinq\";\r\n}\r\n\r\n@@if(conditionInt == 0)\r\n{\r\n    <p>Equals 0</p>\r\n} else if(conditionInt == 1)\r\n{\r\n    <p>Equals 1</p>\r\n} else {\r\n    <p>Equals something else</p>\r\n}\r\n</script></div>\r\n<div id=\"sql_if_ifElseIfElse\" hidden></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n","created":"2025-04-25T06:13:11","changed":"2025-05-08T08:27:51.4364362Z","test_parameters":null,"included_js_libs":"legacy_chartjs"}